BE.gif" ] }</pre> </div> <p>A <b>bee</b> is a flying <a href="/w/Arthropod" title="Arthropod">arthropodan</a> <a href="/w/Neutral_mob" class="mw-redirect" title="Neutral mob">neutral mob</a> that lives in a <a href="/w/Bee_nest" class="mw-redirect" title="Bee nest">bee nest</a> or <a href="/w/Beehive" title="Beehive">beehive</a>, and fills it with harvestable <a href="/w/Honey" class="mw-disambig" title="Honey">honey</a> using nectar it gathers from <a href="/w/Flower" title="Flower">flowers</a>. Attacking a bee, or interfering with its home without proper precautions, causes it and all nearby bees to attack using their stingers. If a bee attacks something, it will lose its stinger and eventually die. </p> <div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" </div> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Spawning">Spawning</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=1&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Spawning" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Spawning"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <p>Bees are the only <a href="/w/Arthropod" title="Arthropod">arthropod</a> mob that can spawn in any <a href="/w/Difficulty" title="Difficulty">difficulty</a> including Peaceful. </p> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Natural_generation">Natural generation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=2&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Natural generation" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Natural generation"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <p>Naturally generated <a href="/w/Bee_nest" class="mw-redirect" title="Bee nest">bee nests</a> generate with 3 bees in them. </p><p>Naturally-generated birch or oak trees have equal chances to generate with a <a href="/w/Bee_nest" class="mw-redirect" title="Bee nest">bee nest</a>, depending on the biome: </p> <table class="wikitable"> <tbody><tr> <th rowspan="2">Biome </th> <th colspan="3&quot;">Chance </th></tr> <tr> <th><b><a href="/w/Java_Edition" title="Java Edition">JE</a></b> </th> <th><b><a </td> <td>0.2% </td> <td>0.035% </td></tr> <tr> <td><span class="nowrap"><span class="sprite-file" style=""><span class="pixel-image" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/w/Cherry_Grove" title="Cherry Grove"><img alt="" src="/images/BiomeSprite_cherry-grove.png?ac8c8" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="16" height="16" class="mw-file-element" data-file-width="16" data-file-height="16" class="mw-headline" id="Saplings">Saplings</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=3&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Saplings" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Saplings"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <p><a href="/w/Birch" title="Birch">Birch</a>, <a href="/w/Cherry" title="Cherry">cherry</a>, and <a href="/w/Oak" title="Oak">oak</a> trees grown from <a href="/w/Sapling" title="Sapling">saplings</a> that are within 2 blocks of any 1- or 2-block tall <a href="/w/Flower" title="Flower">flowers</a>, <a href="/w/Flowering_azalea" class="mw-redirect" title="Flowering azalea">flowering azalea</a>, <a href="/w/Cherry_leaves" class="mw-redirect" title="Cherry leaves">cherry leaves</a>, <a href="/w/Flowering_azalea_leaves" class="mw-redirect" title="Flowering azalea leaves">flowering azalea leaves</a>, <a href="/w/Mangrove_propagule" class="mw-redirect" title="Mangrove propagule">mangrove propagule</a>, <a href="/w/Spore_blossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Spore blossom">spore blossom</a>, <a href="/w/Pink_petals" class="mw-redirect" title="Pink petals">pink petals</a>, or <a href="/w/Chorus_flower" class="mw-redirect" title="Chorus flower">chorus flower</a> have a 5% chance of having a <a href="/w/Bee_nest" class="mw-redirect" title="Bee nest">bee nest</a> containing 2–3 bees. </p><p><a href="/w/Mangrove" title="Mangrove">Mangroves</a> grown from <a href="/w/Mangrove_propagule" class="mw-redirect" title="Mangrove propagule">mangrove propagules</a> have a 1% chance of having a bee nest containing 2-3 bees. Unlike birch, cherry and oak trees, no flowers are required for a bee nest to generate.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>1<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> </p> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Drops">Drops</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=4&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Drops" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Drops"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="On_death">On death</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=5&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: On death" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: On death"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <p>Upon death, adult bees drop <span class="animated"><span class="pixel-image animated-active xp-2" style="background-position:left center;background-size:16px 16px;padding-left:19px;background-repeat:no-repeat"></span><span class="pixel-image xp-6" style="background-position:left center;background-size:16px 16px;padding-left:19px;background-repeat:no-repeat"></span></span>1–3<span class="hidden-alt-text">XP</span> <a href="/w/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a> when killed by a <a href="/w/Player" title="Player">player</a> or a tamed <a href="/w/Wolf" title="Wolf">wolf</a>. Like other baby animals, killing a baby bee yields no experience. </p> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Breeding">Breeding</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=6&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Breeding" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Breeding"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <p>Upon <a href="/w/Breeding" title="Breeding">breeding</a> with any flower successfully, <span class="animated"><span class="pixel-image animated-active xp-2" style="background-position:left center;background-size:16px 16px;padding-left:19px;background-repeat:no-repeat"></span><span class="pixel-image xp-6" style="background-position:left center;background-size:16px 16px;padding-left:19px;background-repeat:no-repeat"></span><span class="pixel-image xp-16" style="background-position:left center;background-size:16px 16px;padding-left:19px;background-repeat:no-repeat"></span></span>1–7<span class="hidden-alt-text">XP</span> is dropped. </p> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Behavior">Behavior</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=7&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Behavior" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Behavior"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <p>Bees do not fly (like <a href="/w/Ghast" title="Ghast">ghasts</a> or the <a href="/w/Ender_dragon" class="mw-redirect" title="Ender dragon">ender dragon</a>), but instead hover a few <a href="/w/Block" title="Block">blocks</a> above the ground similar to <a href="/w/Bat" title="Bat">bats</a> and <a href="/w/Parrot" title="Parrot">parrots</a>. </p><p>Bees are considered <a href="/w/Arthropod" title="Arthropod">arthropods</a> and take increased <a href="/w/Damage" title="Damage">damage</a> from the <a href="/w/Bane_of_Arthropods" title="Bane of Arthropods">Bane of Arthropods</a> enchantment.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-pre&#95;2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-pre-2"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>2<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> They also take damage when touching <a href="/w/Water" title="Water">water</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>3<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> </p><p>Bees can be attached to a <a href="/w/Lead" title="Lead">lead</a>, even when angered. They can still attack while attached. </p><p>Bees usually venture up to 22 <a href="/w/Block" title="Block">blocks</a> from their beehive to collect nectar from a viable plant or to attack someone. Bees can venture farther away if necessary. </p><p>Bees do not take damage from <a href="/w/Sweet_berry_bush" class="mw-redirect" title="Sweet berry bush">sweet berry bushes</a>. </p><p>A bee can fly horizontally and vertically upward through scaffolding but does not fly downward. A bee does not fly through an open trapdoor or regular door on its own (a bee can be led through a <a href="/w/Door" title="Door">door</a> with a flower) but babies can fly through the gap above a fence gate in a 1×2 doorway. In <a href="/w/Java_Edition" title="Java Edition"><i>Java Edition</i></a>, Bees also spin on scaffolding if they are on top of it and cannot go anywhere.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>4<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> </p><p>Despite being flying mobs, bees can destroy <a href="/w/Turtle_egg" class="mw-redirect" title="Turtle egg">turtle eggs</a> when on top of them.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>5<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> </p> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Pollinating">Pollinating</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=8&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Pollinating" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Pollinating"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <p>Bees leave their nest during the day. They fly around <a href="/w/Bee_Nest" title="Bee Nest">their nests</a> and are attracted to <a href="/w/Flower" title="Flower">flowers</a> (except <a href="/w/Closed_eyeblossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Closed eyeblossom">closed eyeblossoms</a>), <a href="/w/Flowering_azalea" class="mw-redirect" title="Flowering azalea">flowering azaleas</a>, <a href="/w/Flowering_azalea_leaves" class="mw-redirect" title="Flowering azalea leaves">flowering azalea leaves</a>, <a href="/w/Mangrove_propagule" class="mw-redirect" title="Mangrove propagule">mangrove propagules</a>, <a href="/w/Pink_petals" class="mw-redirect" title="Pink petals">pink petals</a>, <a href="/w/Cherry_leaves" class="mw-redirect" title="Cherry leaves">cherry leaves</a>, <a href="/w/Spore_blossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Spore blossom">spore blossoms</a>, <a href="/w/Chorus_flower" class="mw-redirect" title="Chorus flower">chorus flowers</a>, <a href="/w/Cactus_flower" class="mw-redirect" title="Cactus flower">cactus flowers</a>, and <a href="/w/Wildflowers" title="Wildflowers">wildflowers</a>, which are the valid plants for the bee to gather nectar from. Bees can gather nectar from <a href="/w/Wither_rose" class="mw-redirect" title="Wither rose">wither roses</a> but receive the <a href="/w/Wither_(effect)" title="Wither (effect)">wither effect</a>. As a result, bees can die.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>6<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Bees can also gather nectar from <a href="/w/Open_eyeblossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Open eyeblossom">open eyeblossoms</a>, but get poisoned as result; they completely ignore <a href="/w/Closed_eyeblossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Closed eyeblossom">closed eyeblossoms</a> and are unable to gather nectar from them. Bees also completely ignore flowers in <a href="/w/Flower_pot" class="mw-redirect" title="Flower pot">flower pots</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>7<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>8<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> </p><p>After circling a flower for more than 400 ticks, a bee collects nectar. However, if the bee gets damaged, it ceases its efforts to collect nectar. A bee carrying nectar has nectar spots on its abdomen and drops nectar <a href="/w/Particle" class="mw-redirect mw-disambig" title="Particle">particles</a> to fertilize plants below the bee. </p><p>Bees that have nectar may pollinate <a href="/w/Wheat_crop" class="mw-redirect" title="Wheat crop">wheat crops</a>, <a href="/w/Potato_crop" class="mw-redirect" title="Potato crop">potato crops</a>, <a href="/w/Carrot_crop" class="mw-redirect" title="Carrot crop">carrot crops</a>, <a href="/w/Beetroot_crop" class="mw-redirect" title="Beetroot crop">beetroot crops</a>, <a href="/w/Melon_stem" class="mw-redirect" title="Melon stem">melon stems</a>, <a href="/w/Sweet_berry_bush" class="mw-redirect" title="Sweet berry bush">sweet berry bushes</a>, <a href="/w/Pumpkin_stem" class="mw-redirect" title="Pumpkin stem">pumpkin stems</a>, <a href="/w/Cave_vines" class="mw-redirect" title="Cave vines">cave vines</a>, <a href="/w/Torchflower_crop" class="mw-redirect" title="Torchflower crop">torchflower crops</a>, and <a href="/w/Pitcher_crop" class="mw-redirect" title="Pitcher crop">pitcher crops</a>&#8204;<sup class="nowrap Inline-Template" title="">[<i><span title="This statement only applies to Bedrock Edition"><a href="/w/Bedrock_Edition" title="Bedrock Edition">Bedrock Edition</a> only</span></i>]</sup> that they fly over. When one of these plants gets pollinated, it advances to another growth stage, similar to using <a href="/w/Bone_meal" class="mw-redirect" title="Bone meal">bone meal</a>. To pollinate a plant, a bee must be 1 to 2 blocks directly above the plant and must have a valid home hive. A bee can fertilize plants 10 times each time they have nectar. There is an approximately 5% chance each tick to attempt fertilization. </p><p>Afterward, the bee flies back into its hive/nest to make honey. It takes about 2 minutes for the bee to do this. </p> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Housing">Housing</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=9&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Housing" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Housing"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/w/File:Bee_and_bee_nest.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="/images/thumb/Bee_and_bee_nest.png/300px-Bee_and_bee_nest.png?289f8" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="300" height="169" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/images/thumb/Bee_and_bee_nest.png/600px-Bee_and_bee_nest.png?289f8 2x" data-file-width="854" data-file-height="480" /></a><figcaption>A bee going into a <a href="/w/Bee_nest" class="mw-redirect" title="Bee nest">bee nest</a>.</figcaption></figure> <div role="note" class="hatnote searchaux">See also: <a href="/w/Tutorial:Honey_farming" title="Tutorial:Honey farming">Tutorial:Honey farming</a> </div> <p>Bees live together in colonies and take any <a href="/w/Bee_nest" class="mw-redirect" title="Bee nest">bee nest</a> or <a href="/w/Beehive" title="Beehive">beehive</a> that has enough space as its home. One bee nest/beehive can house up to 3 bees. Homeless bees search for empty beehives by wandering around generally in a northwest direction. Bees can enter a beehive from any side, but exit only from the front. One-way bee-gates can be made by using this mechanic. </p><p>Bees return to their nest when it <a href="/w/Rain" title="Rain">rains</a> and during the <a href="/w/Night" class="mw-redirect" title="Night">night</a>. This behavior extends to biomes that don't rain, such as the <a href="/w/Desert" title="Desert">desert</a>. They stay in their nest or hive for at least 2400 game ticks (2 minutes) before coming back out. Bees in a nest/hive retain their data (<a href="/w/Health" title="Health">health</a>, name, etc.). </p><p>Breaking a nest or hive without <a href="/w/Silk_Touch" title="Silk Touch">Silk Touch</a> releases all bees contained inside. If the nest or hive is harvested using a tool enchanted with Silk Touch, the bees are contained in the dropped item and can exit the nest/hive when it is placed again. </p><p>When a bee that has nectar enters and then leaves its nest or hive, the honey level of the nest/hive is increased by one; there is a 1% chance it is increased by two. When the honey level of that hive reaches 5, the <a href="/w/Player" title="Player">player</a> can harvest <a href="/w/Honeycomb" title="Honeycomb">honeycombs</a> or <a href="/w/Honey_bottle" class="mw-redirect" title="Honey bottle">honey bottles</a>. The honey level resets back to 0 when a honeycomb or honey bottle is harvested. </p><p>Because there is neither <a href="/w/Daylight_cycle" title="Daylight cycle">daylight cycle</a> nor <a href="/w/Weather" title="Weather">weather</a> in <a href="/w/The_Nether" title="The Nether">the Nether</a> and <a href="/w/The_End" title="The End">the End</a>, bees work without resting in these dimensions. This behavior is distinct from that of the <a href="/w/Villager" title="Villager">villagers</a>, which follow their daily routine according to the time in the <a href="/w/Overworld" title="Overworld">Overworld</a>, regardless of which dimension they are in. </p> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Attacking">Attacking</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=10&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Attacking" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Attacking"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <div role="note" class="hatnote searchaux">Main article: <a href="/w/Damage" title="Damage">Damage</a></div> <p>All bees nearby are angered when an individual bee is attacked (unless the bee attacked is killed in one hit), honey or honeycombs are collected (unless a campfire is placed under the nest), or a bee nest/beehive is destroyed. Even destroying newly-placed uninhabited beehives anger nearby bees. Hitting or walking on a beehive does not anger bees; only destroying it angers them. When destroyed, a beehive releases any bees that it contained. If the beehive is destroyed with a <a href="/w/Silk_Touch" title="Silk Touch">Silk Touch</a> tool, bees kept within the hive remain neutral, while those outside the hive also remain neutral. </p> <figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/w/File:Invisible_stingers.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="/images/thumb/Invisible_stingers.png/300px-Invisible_stingers.png?908f2" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="300" height="169" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/images/thumb/Invisible_stingers.png/600px-Invisible_stingers.png?908f2 2x" data-file-width="854" data-file-height="480" /></a><figcaption>The <a href="/w/Invisibility" title="Invisibility">Invisibility</a> effect does not cause stingers in stung players to disappear.</figcaption></figure> <p>Bees attack and swarm the <a href="/w/Player" title="Player">player</a> as a group when angered, and the eyes of angered bees turn red. Collecting a <a href="/w/Honeycomb" title="Honeycomb">honeycomb</a> or a <a href="/w/Honey_bottle" class="mw-redirect" title="Honey bottle">honey bottle</a> from a nest or hive causes the bees that are currently in that nest or hive to leave and swarm the player unless a <a href="/w/Campfire" title="Campfire">campfire</a> is placed below the hive. Bees attack only once, similar to <a href="/w/Llama" title="Llama">llamas</a>, and non-aggressive <a href="/w/Panda" title="Panda">pandas</a>. </p><p>Bees do not deal any damage in <a href="/w/Peaceful" class="mw-redirect" title="Peaceful">Peaceful</a> difficulty and are completely passive. They fly outside the beehive and search for flowers as usual. </p><p>If the player deflects a bee's attack with a <a href="/w/Shield" title="Shield">shield</a>, the bee continues attacking until it succeeds in hitting the player. </p><p>When a bee's attack on a player succeeds, the player is <a href="/w/Poison" title="Poison">poisoned</a>. A bee loses its stinger after a successful attack, cannot attack further and does not retreat to its nest (even at night), and dies approximately one minute later. This can be delayed with potion <a href="/w/Effect" title="Effect">effects</a> (<a href="/w/Regeneration" title="Regeneration">Regeneration</a>/<a href="/w/Resistance" title="Resistance">Resistance</a>/<a href="/w/Absorption" title="Absorption">Absorption</a>) that have a 255 potency. </p><p>It is possible to (quickly) breed at least one angered bee with another, even if it or they had stung and lost the stinger. However, they remain angered and still die later due to being stingerless. </p><p>Bees also swarm and attack other <a href="/w/Mob" title="Mob">mobs</a> when <a href="/w/Damage" title="Damage">damaged</a>, for example, if a <a href="/w/Skeleton" title="Skeleton">skeleton</a> accidentally shoots a bee. </p><p>Bees become neutral if they fail to land a hit on their target within 25 seconds. </p> <ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional"> <li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px"> <div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/w/File:Bee_stings.gif" class="mw-file-description" title="The stinging animation; the bee can remain upside down for longer periods of time if a distance is kept."><img alt="The stinging animation; the bee can remain upside down for longer periods of time if a distance is kept." src="/images/thumb/Bee_stings.gif/120px-Bee_stings.gif?dc38a" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="120" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/images/Bee_stings.gif?dc38a 2x" data-file-width="150" data-file-height="150" /></a></span></div> <div class="gallerytext">The stinging animation; the bee can remain upside down for longer periods of time if a distance is kept.</div> </li> <li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px"> <div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/w/File:Bee_(sting).png" class="mw-file-description" title="Prior to stinging"><img alt="Prior to stinging" src="/images/thumb/Bee_%28sting%29.png/120px-Bee_%28sting%29.png?aa27c" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="120" height="102" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/images/thumb/Bee_%28sting%29.png/240px-Bee_%28sting%29.png?aa27c 2x" data-file-width="836" data-file-height="711" /></a></span></div> <div class="gallerytext">Prior to stinging</div> </li> <li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px"> <div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/w/File:Bee_(stingless).png" class="mw-file-description" title="After stinging"><img alt="After stinging" src="/images/thumb/Bee_%28stingless%29.png/120px-Bee_%28stingless%29.png?8b4bc" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="120" height="102" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/images/thumb/Bee_%28stingless%29.png/240px-Bee_%28stingless%29.png?8b4bc 2x" data-file-width="836" data-file-height="711" /></a></span></div> <div class="gallerytext">After stinging</div> </li> </ul> <p>In <a href="/w/Java_Edition" title="Java Edition"><i>Java Edition</i></a>, a bee's stinger is visible on the player as a small black dot after the bee successfully attacked. </p> <ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional"> <li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px"> <div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/w/File:Steve_got_stung.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="/images/thumb/Steve_got_stung.png/111px-Steve_got_stung.png?e694e" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="111" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/images/thumb/Steve_got_stung.png/222px-Steve_got_stung.png?e694e 2x" data-file-width="636" data-file-height="688" /></a></span></div> <div class="gallerytext"></div> </li> </ul> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Breeding_2">Breeding</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=11&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Breeding" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Breeding"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <div role="note" class="hatnote searchaux">Main article: <a href="/w/Breeding" title="Breeding">Breeding</a></div> <p>Bees follow <a href="/w/Player" title="Player">players</a> holding any 1- or 2-block tall <a href="/w/Flower" title="Flower">flowers</a> (except <a href="/w/Closed_eyeblossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Closed eyeblossom">closed eyeblossom</a>), <a href="/w/Mangrove_propagule" class="mw-redirect" title="Mangrove propagule">mangrove propagules</a>, <a href="/w/Flowering_azalea" class="mw-redirect" title="Flowering azalea">flowering azaleas</a>, <a href="/w/Flowering_azalea_leaves" class="mw-redirect" title="Flowering azalea leaves">flowering azalea leaves</a>, <a href="/w/Cherry_leaves" class="mw-redirect" title="Cherry leaves">cherry leaves</a>, <a href="/w/Pink_petals" class="mw-redirect" title="Pink petals">pink petals</a>, <a href="/w/Wildflowers" title="Wildflowers">wildflowers</a>, <a href="/w/Spore_blossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Spore blossom">spore blossoms</a>, <a href="/w/Cactus_flower" class="mw-redirect" title="Cactus flower">cactus flowers</a> or <a href="/w/Chorus_flower" class="mw-redirect" title="Chorus flower">chorus flowers</a>. If the player is standing still and being followed by bees, the bees go toward the player, face the player, and rest on the ground. They do this until the player moves. </p><p>If bees are given any of the blocks listed above (except <a href="/w/Open_eyeblossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Open eyeblossom">open eyeblossom</a> and <a href="/w/Wither_rose" class="mw-redirect" title="Wither rose">wither rose</a>), they enter love mode and pair up to create baby bees, granting the <a href="/w/Player" title="Player">player</a> 1-7 <a href="/w/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a>. The parent bees have a cooldown of 5 minutes (6000 ticks) before they can be <a href="/w/Breeding" title="Breeding">bred</a> again. Babies take 20 minutes (1 in-game day) to grow up. The growth of baby bees can be accelerated using flowers; each use reduces the remaining time by 10%. However, bees' growth timer and breeding cooldowns are frozen while working in a hive; thus, when rapidly growing a population, it may be desirable to temporarily remove the hives. </p><p><a href="/w/Wither_rose" class="mw-redirect" title="Wither rose">Wither roses</a> and <a href="/w/Open_eyeblossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Open eyeblossom">open eyeblossoms</a> cannot be used for breeding bees or growing baby bees. Feeding a bee a wither rose inflicts it with the <a href="/w/Wither_(effect)" title="Wither (effect)">Wither</a> effect for 2 seconds (40 <a href="/w/Game_tick" class="mw-redirect" title="Game tick">game ticks</a>), while feeding a bee an open eyeblossom inflicts it with <a href="/w/Poison" title="Poison">Poison</a> for 1.25 seconds (25 <a href="/w/Game_tick" class="mw-redirect" title="Game tick">game ticks</a>). <a href="/w/Closed_eyeblossom" class="mw-redirect" title="Closed eyeblossom">Closed eyeblossoms</a> cannot be used to lead, breed or grow bees. </p> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sounds">Sounds</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=12&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Sounds" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Sounds"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <p><i><a href="/w/Java_Edition" title="Java Edition">Java Edition</a></i>: </p> <table class="wikitable collapsible" data-description="Sound"><tbody><tr><th colspan="9">Sounds</th></tr><tr><th>Sound</th><th><a href="/w/Closed_captions" title="Closed captions">Closed captions</a></th><th><span class="explain" title="The category this sound falls into; what volume slider controls this sound in the Music and Sounds menu.">Source</span></th><th><span class="explain" title="When the game calls this sound event.">Description</span></th><th><a href="/w/Identifier" title="Identifier">Identifier</a></th><th>Translation key</th><th>Volume</th><th>Pitch</th><th>Attenuation<br />distance</th></tr><tr><td rowspan="1"><span class="sound"><span class="sound-title"></span><span class="mw-default-size sound-audio" typeof="mw:File"><span><audio id="mwe_player_45" preload="none" href="/w/Java_Edition" title="Java Edition">Java Edition</a></i>: </p> <div role="note" class="hatnote searchaux">Main article: <a href="/w/Entity_format" title="Entity format">Entity format</a></div> <div class="treeview"> <ul><li><span title="NBT Compound / JSON Object"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-48px -16px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[NBT Compound / JSON Object]</span></span> Entity data <ul><li class="mw-empty-elt"></li><li class="treeview-header nbttree-inherited load-page" data-page="Template:Nbt inherit/angerable/template" data-template="true" data-treeview="true" data-treeviewclass="nbttree-inherited">Additional fields for mobs that can become angry<span class="mw-empty-elt"></li><li class="treeview-header nbttree-inherited load-page" data-page="Template:Nbt inherit/breedable/template" data-template="true" data-treeview="true" data-treeviewclass="nbttree-inherited">Additional fields for mobs that can breed<span class="noscript"> see <a href="/w/Template:Nbt_inherit/breedable/template" title="Template:Nbt inherit/entity/template" data-template="true" data-treeview="true" data-treeviewclass="nbttree-inherited">Tags common to all entities<span class="noscript"> see <a href="/w/Template:Nbt_inherit/entity/template" title="Template:Nbt inherit/entity/template">Template:Nbt inherit/entity/template</a></span></li> <li class="mw-empty-elt"></li><li class="treeview-header nbttree-inherited load-page" data-page="Template:Nbt inherit/mob/template" data-template="true" data-treeview="true" data-treeviewclass="nbttree-inherited">Tags common to all mobs<span class="noscript"> see <a href="/w/Template:Nbt_inherit/mob/template" title="Template:Nbt inherit/mob/template">Template:Nbt inherit/mob/template</a></span></li> <li><span title="Int"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-48px -0px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[Int]</span></span><span class="nowrap" style="font-weight: bold;">&#160;CannotEnterHiveTicks</span>: Time left in ticks until the bee can enter a beehive. Used when the bee is angered and released from the hive by a player, but the hive is smoked by a <a href="/w/Campfire" title="Campfire">campfire</a>.</li> <li><span title="Int"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-48px -0px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[Int]</span></span><span class="nowrap" style="font-weight: bold;">&#160;CropsGrownSincePollination</span>: How many crops the bee has grown since its last pollination. Used to limit number of crops it can grow.</li> <li><span title="Int Array"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-16px -32px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[Int Array]</span></span><span class="nowrap" style="font-weight: bold;">&#160;flower_pos</span>: Block location, as 3 integers, of the flower that the bee is circling.</li> <li><span title="Boolean"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-48px -32px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[Boolean]</span></span><span class="nowrap" style="font-weight: bold;">&#160;HasNectar</span>: 1 or 0 (true/false) - true if the bee is carrying nectar.</li> <li><span title="Boolean"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-48px -32px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[Boolean]</span></span><span class="nowrap" style="font-weight: bold;">&#160;HasStung</span>: 1 or 0 (true/false) - true if the bee has stung a mob or player.</li> <li><span title="Int Array"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-16px -32px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[Int Array]</span></span><span class="nowrap" style="font-weight: bold;">&#160;hive_pos</span>: Block location, as 3 integers, of the bee's <a href="/w/Bee_hive" class="mw-redirect" title="Bee hive">hive</a>.</li> <li><span title="Int"><span class="sprite nbt-sprite" style="background-position:-48px -0px;background-size:64px auto;height:16px;width:16px"></span><span class="hidden-alt-text">[Int]</span></span><span class="nowrap" style="font-weight: bold;">&#160;TicksSincePollination</span>: Number of ticks passed since the bee's last pollination.</li></ul></li></ul> </div> <p><i><a href="/w/Bedrock_Edition" title="Bedrock Edition">Bedrock Edition</a></i>: </p> <dl><dd>See <a href="/w/Bedrock_Edition_level_format/Entity_format" <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Issues">Issues</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=22&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Issues" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Issues"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <p>Issues relating to "Bee" are maintained on the <a href="/w/Bug_tracker" title="Bug tracker">bug tracker</a>. Issues should be reported and viewed <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" class="external text" href="https://bugs.mojang.com/issues/?jql=project%20in%20%28MC%2C%20MCPE%29%20AND%20%28resolution%20is%20EMPTY%20OR%20resolution%20in%20%281%2C%202%2C%206%29%29%20AND%20%28summary%20~%20%22Bee%22%29%20ORDER%20BY%20resolution%20DESC">there</a>. </p> <div class="issue-list" data-mc="&quot;Confirmation Status&quot; != Unconfirmed AND (resolution is EMPTY OR (resolution = &quot;Fixed&quot; AND affectedVersion = &quot;1.21.10&quot;)) AND (summary ~ &quot;Bee&quot;) ORDER BY resolution ASC, &quot;Mojang Priority&quot; ASC, &quot;Votes Count&quot; DESC, key ASC" data-mcpe="&quot;Confirmation Status&quot; != Unconfirmed AND resolution is EMPTY AND (summary ~ &quot;Bee&quot;) ORDER BY &quot;Votes Count&quot; DESC, key ASC"></div> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Trivia">Trivia</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=23&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Trivia" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Trivia"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <ul><li>Bees were made to be half a <a href="/w/Block" title="Block">block</a> in size because <a href="/w/Mojang_Studios" title="Mojang Studios">Mojang</a> considered this size to be the cutest.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-19" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-19"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>15<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li> <li>Bees pollinate the top half of <a href="/w/Sunflower" title="Sunflower">sunflowers</a>.</li> <li>In reality, juvenile bees are helpless, worm-like larvae, not smaller versions of adults.</li> <li>Also in reality, bees collect both nectar and pollen by pollinating flowers. The pollen is used as a primary food source by the bee colony, but has little direct importance to the formation of honey, which is made from the nectar and serves as another food source. Also, in real life, bees are scared of smoke and don't exit the nest or hive.</li> <li>However, bees losing their stingers and dying after attacking the player is consistent with real bees, as in reality their stingers are barbed and attached to vital organs, so the stinger gets stuck and causes fatal injuries to the bee once it tries to fly away and the stinger detaches.</li></ul> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Gallery">Gallery</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=24&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Gallery" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Gallery"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Renders">Renders</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=25&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Renders" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Renders"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Idle">Idle</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Bee?section=26&amp;veaction=edit" title="Edit section: Idle" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Bee?action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section&#039;s source code: Idle"><span>edit source</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4> <ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional"> <li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px"> <div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;
